parameters: Noble Kasaro: Hoho, this is my secret weapon!

Noble Kasaro: It's not just a ship! It can carry three
giant crystals!

Mage Relm: Are you planning to make the fastest ship? With
such huge crystals, there could be better uses for them...

Noble Kasaro: I won't use something so trivial. I want to
make this ship float in the sky, not on water!

Noble Kasaro: A ship that soars through the sky! Making an
airship is my dream!

Thief Nora: A-a ship that flies through the sky...! That's
amazing, I want to ride it!

Noble Kasaro: Welcome, welcome! I warmly welcome any
comrades who understand this dream!

Priestess Sophia: Flying in the sky, is that even
possible?

Mage Relm: That's impossible, right?! If it were
achievable, the Imperial Army would have already adopted
it!

Mage Relm: This is why amateurs are troublesome! Magic is
not all-powerful!

Noble Kasaro: I heard that there is a genius at the Magic
Academy, so I wanted to talk to you all about it...

Noble Kasaro: If even with a genius it seems impossible,
then there's no choice but to give up on this dream...

Mage Relm: I-I won't fall for such a cheap provocation! As
a researcher, I believe in acknowledging the impossible!

Clea: I think that making the impossible possible is
something that we can do too.

Clea: I want to help Noble Kasaro with his dream, not just
as a member of the guild, but as an individual too.
Noble Kasaro: What is your goal, Clea?
Clea: It is to find and kill dragons.

Noble Kasaro: Indeed, it is an immense goal. But if you are
willing to help me, I will also support your goal.

Noble Kasaro: I wonder, genius mages? This old man should
be able to offer you a lot of help.

Mage Relm: I-I understand! I don't know anything about
money, is that okay!?

Mage Relm: I don't feel like it, but I'll cooperate with
Dokusa-san... Ugh, it seems like I'm going to be burdened
with another troublesome task...

Noble Kasaro: Hoho, it's settled then! I will wait for good
news at the mansion.

Noble Kasaro: If you're okay with it, please use this. It's
a small token of gratitude for your cooperation.

Noble Kasaro: Oh, you're back! So, is it possible to
develop an airship?

Clea: We were able to obtain the cooperation of the Magic
Academy.

Researcher Caron: I am Caron, a member of the Magic
Academy. I will explain the details to you.

Mage Relm: C-Caron-san!? How did you find this place so
easily?

Researcher Caron: As an Archmage, I was able to see through
your intentions. Although I am a novice, please allow me to
pursue your dream together.

Noble Kasaro: Those are kind words. Tell me anything you
need to pursue our dream together.

Noble Kasaro: This foolish dream of flying this thing in
the sky, but with comrades, it will surely come true!

Mage Relm: Yes, that's right! There's no dream that should
be denied!

Clea: Understood. When the instructions are given, we will
dispatch a senior mage.

Researcher Caron: I'll leave it to you. Once the path is
clear, please gather them.

Noble Kasaro: I will leave that request to the Adventurer's
Guild. You all are accomplices to this dream, so you must
definitely get on the ship.
Clea: Yes, I'm looking forward to it.

Noble Kasaro: It seems that the preparations are complete.
Finally, this ship will take to the sky!

Noble Kasaro: I appreciate your cooperation up until today.
Let us fly through the sky together and leave our names in
history.
Clea: Yes, it is an honor to be able to accompany you.

Noble Kasaro: When you're ready, please talk to me. I don't
know what will happen, so be prepared.

Noble Kasaro: The secret to longevity is the lively
interaction with young people.

Noble Kasaro: Very well, let us wait for a while until dawn
and embark on an adventure like no one has ever experienced
before!
Noble Kasaro: This is the real deal, now get on the ship!!

Noble Kasaro: I had a feeling you would come. How about we
talk while looking at the lake?

Noble Kasaro: Looking back, my life since meeting you all
has been filled with adventure, excitement, friendship, and
joy... It has truly been enjoyable.

Noble Kasaro: I sailed the ship, saw the same scenery as my
son, and fought dragons.

Clea: For us, it was truly wonderful days of adventure.
Whenever we think back on our journey, Noble Kasaro is
always there.

Noble Kasaro: Hahaha, that's great! I wonder what kind of
face Kasaro in our memories is making?

Clea: You always have a smile on your face. Just thinking
about it warms my heart.

Noble Kasaro: Perhaps deep down in my heart... I have done
things with you all that I couldn't do with my son.

Noble Kasaro: However, from here on out, it's going to be
different! I've decided to fight for you all, not as a
substitute for something else.

Noble Kasaro: I have received information that the nobles
who support Queen Caron are surrounding the Fotizona
Palace.

Noble Kasaro: We will definitely stop them, with the help
of the Emma Thieves and, oh, the Emma Mercenary Corps too.
Clea: Thank you so much for always helping us.

Noble Kasaro: I cannot go to the site myself, but I will
respond with my words as they are...

Noble Kasaro: Remember that my heart is always with you
all.

Clea: Yes, understood. I will bring Kasaro-san's heart with
me to the battlefield.

Noble Kasaro: New memories can only be created by the
living. No matter what happens, make sure to survive.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Clea: Thank you so much for always helping us.

Noble Kasaro: I can't go to the site myself, but I'll

Noble Kasaro: Remember that my heart is always with you.

Clea: Yes, understood. I will bring Noble Kasaro's heart
with me to the battlefield.

Noble Kasaro: It might be a good idea to seek cooperation
from High Priest Raoko, who I've heard has a connection with
the shrine maidens.

Noble Kasaro: ...I won't allow you to die. Going first is
the privilege of the elderly.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Researcher Caron: My dream will come true! I will
definitely make this ship fly!

events.name: ドラゴンの翼自動実行

parameters:
Researcher Caron: Thanks to all of you, we were saved! It
was unexpected for such a strange bird to appear.

Researcher Caron: By the way... Did any of you hear
something like a strange chirping sound? Do you know
anything about it?

Researcher Caron: You are our saviors. If anything happens,
please let us know.

Noble Kasaro: Thank you so much for fulfilling my dream and
saving my life. I can't express my gratitude enough.
Clea: What will Kasaro-san do from now on?

Noble Kasaro: That's right... I will pursue something new,
a new dream, by meeting young new companions. Life is long!

Noble Kasaro: Once your mission is over, come back here
again. Let's go fishing together.
Clea: Yes... I appreciate your thoughtfulness.

Clea: Excuse me, please let me be alone for a little
while.
Noble Kasaro: What did you see in the sky...?

Mage Relm: It's a dragon... I was skeptical too! But it
really exists, it was definitely flying in the sky.

Priestess Sophia: The one who defeated the giant monster
bird was a dragon. It's fortunate that the flying ship
wasn't targeted...

Thief Nora: Clea-san... she looked like she was in pain...
she was laughing, but she was also crying... she seems to be
suffering...

Noble Kasaro: Clea may have a purpose, but she doesn't have
a dream. If she fulfills her purpose, she will be left
empty.

Noble Kasaro: I want you all by her side to help her find
her dream. This is not a request from a noble, but from a
fellow human being.

Thief Nora: Yes, understood! I want to repay Clea-san's
kindness!

Noble Kasaro: Speaking of repaying kindness... next, I will
assist you with your objective.

Noble Kasaro: If you have any troubles, I want you to rely
on me without fail. Also, if it's alright, please take this
with you.

Noble Kasaro: Oh divine god Sol... Please watch over the
journey of these adventurers with compassion.
実績 英雄の歌：巨大怪鳥討伐

events.note: 確認用であるが、デバッグ終了までは消してはダメ
